====== 网海拾贝 2012-05 (expect,gnu screen/tmux, ipython, virtualenv, emacs...) ======

==== Expect/PExpect ====
	* [[http://www.ibm.com/developerworks/cn/aix/library/au-expect/index.html|Expect 在网络管理中发挥着重要作用]]
	* [[http://www.ibm.com/developerworks/cn/linux/l-cn-firmupgrade/|通过 Shell 和 Expect 脚本实现对 IBM 刀片服务器高级管理模块固件的大量升级]]
	* [[http://www.ibm.com/developerworks/cn/linux/l-cn-pexpect1/|探索 Pexpect，第 1 部分：剖析 Pexpect]]
	* [[http://www.ibm.com/developerworks/cn/linux/l-cn-pexpect2/|探索 Pexpect，第 2 部分：Pexpect 的实例分析]]
	* [[http://topdog.za.net/2012/04/25/python-modules-you-should-know:-pexpect|Python modules you should know: pexpect]]

==== gnu-screen/tmux ====
	* GNU screen
		* [[http://www.ibm.com/developerworks/cn/aix/library/au-gnu_screen/|对话 UNIX: 使用 Screen 创建并管理多个 shell]]
		* [[http://blog.solrex.org/articles/gnu-screen-tips.html|Shell Tips: GNU Screen 的一些小技巧]]
		* [[http://roclinux.cn/?p%3D1742|gnu screen快捷键速查表 ]]
		* [[http://shebang.brandonmintern.com/tips-for-remote-unix-work-ssh-screen-and-vnc|Tips for Remote Unix Work (SSH, screen, and VNC) - #! (shebang)]]

	* tmux: 功能上类似GNU screen, 但为BSD协议，部分功能比GNU screen更强
		* [[http://wowubuntu.com/tmux.html|Tmux : GNU Screen 的替代品 (软件) ]]
		* [[http://blog.csdn.net/yjj1s/article/details/6413172|tmux 配置 & 使用 - yjj1s的专栏 - 博客频道 - CSDN.NET]]
		* [[http://superuser.com/questions/209437/how-do-i-scroll-in-tmux|bash - How do I scroll in tmux? - Super User]]
    {{./tmux.png}}
	* Byobu 是对gnu screen和tmux做的封装和二次开发
		* [[http://unixlab.blogspot.com/2009/11/enhancing-terminals-with-byobu-on.html|Experimenting with GNU/Linux: Enhancing terminals with byobu on Ubuntu 9.10]]
		* [[http://www.webupd8.org/2009/11/byobu-pimps-your-linux-terminal.html|Byobu Pimps Your Linux Terminal ~ Web Upd8: Ubuntu / Linux blog]]
    {{./byobu.png}}

==== Python ====

	* IPython
		* [[http://ipython.org/ipython-doc/rel-0.12/parallel/index.html|Using IPython for parallel computing — IPython v0.12 documentation]]
		* [[http://web.mit.edu/stardev/cluster/docs/latest/plugins/ipython.html|IPython Cluster Plugin ¶]]
		* v0.12版本的新功能之一: Qt Console
			* [[http://ipython.org/ipython-doc/rel-0.12/interactive/qtconsole.html|A Qt Console for IPython — IPython v0.12 documentation]]
		* v0.12版本的新功能之二: IPython notebook (以浏览器为界面，matplotlib绘图直接嵌入显示)
			* [[http://shahuwang.com/?p%3D780|ipython notebook——超级强大的工具 ]]
			* [[http://blog.fperez.org/2012/01/ipython-notebook-historical.html|The IPython notebook: a historical retrospective]]

	* 关于自省/调试的一些新内容
		* [[http://ibm.com/developerworks/cn/linux/l-cn-pythondebugger|Python 代码调试技巧 - IBM developerWorks 中国]]
		* [[http://ibm.com/developerworks/cn/linux/l-pyint/index.html|Python 自省指南 - IBM developerWorks 中国]]
		* [[https://stripe.com/blog/exploring-python-using-gdb|Exploring Python Using GDB]]
		* [[http://showmedo.com/videotutorials/video?name%3DpythonBernsteinPydbIntro&fromSeriesID%3D28|Introducing the pydb Debugger video tutorial]]
		* [[http://winpdb.org/2010/09/rconsole-remote-python-console|rconsole - Remote Python (winpdb)]]
		* [[http://code.google.com/p/iep/|iep - the Interactive Editor for Python]]
				* The shells runs in a ***subprocess*** and can therefore be interrupted or killed.
				* *Multiple shells* can be used at the same time, and can be of ***different Python versions*** (from v2.4 to 3.x)
				* Support for using several ***GUI toolkits*** interactively: PySide, PyQt4, wx, fltk, GTK, Tk.
				* Supports ***magic commands*** similar to IPython

	* VirtualEnv
		* [[http://static.matthewlmcclure.com/s/2012/06/05/emacs-tramp-python-virtualenv.html|Python Development In A VM Using Emacs And Virtualenv]]
		* [[http://blog.fruiapps.com/2012/06/An-introductory-tutorial-to-python-virtualenv-and-virtualenvwrapper|An introductory tutorial to python virtualenv and virtualenvwrapper]]

        • Misc
		* [[http://blog.csdn.net/myzhan/article/details/7269471|Python中的lambda, map, reduce和filter - Myzhan的日积月累]]
		* [[http://ibm.com/developerworks/cn/linux/l-cn-perl2python|Perl 与 Python 之间的一些异同 - IBM developerWorks 中国]]
		* [[http://sophomoredev.com/2012/06/how-i-deploy-with-fabric|How I deploy with Fabric]] (keywords: ssh, devops)


